
Function: ZILOPEN

Syntax:   (ZILOPEN file1 arg2)

 file1 (required, evaluated) - a file name.
 arg2  (required, evaluated) - a fixnum.

Returns:

 Whatever OPEN is defined to return, after doing what OPEN is supposed
 to do with file1.  The type of file access is determined by arg2.

Processing:

 See OPEN for processing.

 arg2 is a fixnum that determines the type of file access.  Its contents
 are system-dependent.

Errors signaled:

 See OPEN for errors.

Notes:

 This function underlies OPEN.

 See member $FILE for more information on file names.

Examples:

 ; None.  Use OPEN, not this internal function whose processing of
 ; arg2 could change at any time.

